Text.SourceString: You’re <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=smile>I heard about you. I heard you’re looking for some fresh air away from the city.
Well, I think you came to the right place.//I hope you find it here.//<portrait=daydreaming>Fresh air, peace of mind, whatever it might be.
One thing I can tell you, <PlayerName>$player</>, rancher to rancher.//You need to talk to your animals to connect with them.
Animals, they’re not much different from us.//<portrait=smile>My dad taught me that.
Wow. You lead such a busy life.//Remember to take a break and communicate with nature.
Communicate your needs and wants all the way to your soul, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>And let nature decide your next steps. That’s what I do.
What a wonderful day!//It’s going to be a great week.
I just knew it.
For sure, the cows appreciate it when I play the flute.//I like to think it relaxes them.
My friends <NpcName>Pablo</> and <NpcName>Rafael</> are very talented blacksmiths.//<portrait=smile>They’re my go-to experts when the ranch needs any tools fixed.
The boys make durable weapons too.//Mom always puts in a good word for them.
I don’t carry a weapon or heavy armor around in my bag, only wooden flutes.//Harmless instruments.
And maybe a handful of soybeans.

<NpcName>Pablo</> and <NpcName>Rafael</> are good friends of mine.//They’re very talented blacksmiths, living right across from the taco truck.//<portrait=smile>You could say they’re my go-to experts.
The boys make durable weapons too.//Mom always puts in a good word for them.
You can collect wild vegetables and cook them.//Go ahead!
Or, if you’re anything like me, you can just eat those vegetables raw. Less work!
I don’t carry a weapon or heavy armor around in my bag, only wooden flutes.//Harmless instruments.
And maybe a handful of soybeans.
Wow. You lead such a busy life. Remember to take a break and communicate with nature.
Communicate your needs and wants all the way to your soul, <PlayerName>$player</>. And let nature decide your next steps. That’s what I do.

<NpcName>Pablo</> and <NpcName>Rafael</> are good friends of mine.//They’re very talented blacksmiths, living right across from the taco truck.//<portrait=smile>You could say they’re my go-to experts.
The boys make durable weapons too.//Mom always puts in a good word for them.
The cows appreciate it when I play the flute.//<portrait=smile>I like to think it relaxes them.
One thing I can tell you, <PlayerName>$player</>, rancher to rancher.//You need to talk to your animals to connect with them.
Animals, they’re not much different from us.//<portrait=smile>My dad taught me that.
The cows appreciate it when I play the flute...oh yeah, for sure!//<portrait=smile>I like to think it relaxes them.
Wow. You lead such a busy life.//Remember to take a break and communicate with nature.
Communicate your needs and wants all the way to your soul, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>And let nature decide your next steps. That’s what I do.
You can collect wild vegetables and cook them.//Go ahead!
Or, if you’re anything like me, you can just eat those vegetables raw.//<portrait=laugh>Less work!
I don’t carry a weapon or heavy armor around in my bag, only wooden flutes.//Harmless instruments.
And maybe a handful of soybeans.
Make sure to keep your animals inside when it rains, will you?
I have no worries when I’m around you. You seem like a loving person.//<portrait=normal>You just have that aura.
Mom is a retired hunter, but she’s always on high alert.//<portrait=concerned>She’d go back into combat in a heartbeat, if necessary.
I don’t know. Any emergency.//<portrait=sad>I won’t jinx it.//<portrait=laugh>Don’t you worry, <PlayerName>$player</>! We’ll be just fine.
You can grow your own animal feed by growing grass on your farm.//<portrait=concerned>Has anyone told you about that?//<portrait=normal>It can save you a lot of money.
But grass doesn’t grow in Winter.//Well, most plants don’t. So…//<portrait=laugh>That’s when the ranch comes in handy.
I don’t really go to the beach unless there’s an important event going on.//<portrait=sad>Yeah, no.
No reason. I guess I just don’t have the drive to go to the beach that much.
Ah, I might go to Fishensips this weekend.//<portrait=normal>I don’t know…//Will you be there?
Have you ever looked at the sky and wondered what’s out there?
I spend a lot of my free time doing just that.//<portrait=daydreaming>Looking at the sky, letting my mind wander…//<portrait=normal>This world sometimes feels too small for my imagination.
Mom is a retired hunter, but she’s always on high alert.//<portrait=concerned>She’d go back into combat in a heartbeat, if necessary.
I don’t know. Any emergency.//<portrait=sad>I won’t jinx it.//<portrait=laugh>Don’t you worry, <PlayerName>$player</>! We’ll be just fine.
I don’t really go to the beach unless there’s an important event going on.//<portrait=sad>Yeah, no.
No reason. I guess I just don’t have the drive to go to the beach that much.
I don’t really go to the beach unless there’s an important event going on.
I learned this from my granddad.//So, once you have animals, make sure to talk to them every day. It’s all they need.//<portrait=concerned>And food...you get that, right?
And don’t forget to feed them, of course!//<portrait=normal>I hope that one is obvious.
Ah, I might go to Fishensips this weekend.//<portrait=normal>I don’t know…//Will you be there?
You can grow your own animal feed by growing grass on your farm.//<portrait=concerned>Has anyone told you about that?//<portrait=normal>It can save you a lot of money.
But grass doesn’t grow in Winter. //Well, most plants don’t. So…//<portrait=laugh>That’s when the ranch comes in handy.
Make sure to keep your animals inside when it rains, yeah?
I have no worries when I’m around you. You seem like a loving person.//<portrait=normal>You just have that aura.
I don’t really go to the beach unless there’s an important event going on.
I learned this from my granddad.//So, once you have animals, make sure to talk to them every day. It’s all they need.//<portrait=concerned>And food...you get that, right?
It’s the weekend again!//<portrait=smile>Anything exciting happening?
Yeah, my week was good.//<portrait=normal>Same old, same old, though.//What about you?//I hope your week was good too.
Have you ever looked at the sky and wondered what’s out there?
I spend a lot of my free time doing just that. Looking at the sky, letting my mind wander… This world sometimes feels too small for my imagination.
Have you ever looked at the sky and wondered what’s out there?
I spend a lot of my free time doing just that.//<portrait=daydreaming>Looking at the sky, letting my mind wander…//<portrait=normal>This world sometimes feels too small for my imagination.
You can grow your own animal feed by growing grass on your farm.//<portrait=concerned>Has anyone told you about that?//<portrait=normal>It can save you a lot of money.
But grass doesn’t grow in Winter.//Well, most plants don’t. So…//<portrait=laugh>That’s when the ranch comes in handy.
Make sure to keep your animals inside when it rains, yeah?
I have no worries when I’m around you. You seem like a loving person.//<portrait=normal>You just have that aura.
Kombucha is the best drink to have with lunch...love it, yeah?//Especially when it’s sunny out. It has that refreshing kick, you know?
I prefer to have my lunch break outdoors. Be one with nature, yeah? When the weather permits, that is.
Hmm… When my mouth can’t find the words, I rely on my flute to do the talking.
Sometimes there’s no other way to do it. Words aren’t enough.
I have to say…I’m a little surprised to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
A pleasant surprise, that is. A very pleasant surprise.//As if the universe wants us to spend the day together. Do you believe in <Italic>things</> like that?
I have to say…I’m a little surprised to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
A pleasant surprise, that is. A very pleasant surprise.//As if the universe wants us to spend the day together. Do you believe in <Italic>things</> like that?
Oh yeah, love it. Kombucha is the best drink to have with lunch. Especially when it’s sunny out. It has that refreshing kick, you know?
I’m not a fan of processed foods. I read somewhere that they’re engineered to make us addicted to them.
How scary is that?
I’m not a fan of processed foods. I read somewhere that they’re engineered to make us addicted to them.
How scary is that?
The more I think about us – humans – the sadder I get.//We put chemicals in our food… Some of us put each other down for no reason at all… Disappointing behavior.
*sighs*
Hmm… When my mouth can’t find the words, I rely on my flute to do the talking.
Sometimes there’s no other way to do it. Words aren’t enough.
The more I think about us – humans – the sadder I get.//We put chemicals in our food… Some of us put each other down for no reason at all… Disappointing behavior.
*sighs*
I don’t like processed foods, but I’m not gonna lie, I eat them once in a while.
I just get really sleepy afterward. Not a great feeling at all. Blech!
I don’t like processed foods, but I’m not gonna lie, I eat them once in a while.
I just get really sleepy afterward. Not a great feeling at all. Blech!
I went to town yesterday and saw a drilling corporation is moving its offices to Coral Island.//<portrait=concerned>I’m disappointed, to be honest.
It was a shock, really.//I had no idea they were buying properties here. What will they make of Coral Island, I wonder?
I hope Pufferfish changes their mind.//<portrait=sad>All I sense from this is negativity.
Is Pufferfish building a mini golf area in front of their office?//<portrait=annoyed>Ugh… I kind of want to play.
Wild fruit and mushrooms are gifts of nature.//They’re so easy to find around here.

Mom used to slay monsters for a living, but she doesn’t anymore.//<portrait=normal>She thinks the island is safe for now, so she just keeps an eye on the cavern.//She never let me play around there… Monster infested, she said.

My parents and I have different views on some things, but I’m glad they’re respectful of my opinions.//<portrait=normal>For example, my parents don’t celebrate birthdays, but they don’t force that view on me. I celebrate mine, all right!//Spring 9 baby here!
Being a first-time farmer must be challenging. There’s a lot to get used to, huh?
My parents had me when they were relatively young.//Because of that, I feel like we’re speaking the same language most of the time.//There isn’t much of a generation gap.
The gap? Oh… I just mean it’s easy to tell my parents how I feel about stuff. Or, you know, just to communicate in general.
Another year has begun. These cherry blossom petals are a beautiful reminder.
Are you close to <NPCName>Macy</>?//<portrait=normal>I believe it’s her birthday tomorrow.
She’s a beautiful soul with a big soft spot for animals.
Are you close to <NPCName>Macy</>?//<portrait=normal>I believe it’s her birthday tomorrow.
She’s a beautiful soul with a big soft spot for animals.
I try to stay away from animal products as much as I can.
We had to take care of an injured cow this morning.//<portrait=sad>I think she’s going to make it, but it’ll be close.
Has that ever happened at your farm?
Spring is my favorite time of year!//<portrait=normal>The flowers are opening up, the fawns are learning to walk… It feels like everything is waking up after Winter.
I’ve always loved that my birthday falls in Spring.//<portrait=daydreaming>It feels like nature is putting on a show for me.
Even if I weren’t here, the natural world would keep on going without me.//<portrait=normal>I know that sounds bad, but it’s a strange comfort to me.
Have you planted any Spring flowers, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=laugh>Make sure your animals don’t snack on them!
There are so many delicious things you can grow in Spring!//<portrait=daydreaming>My mouth is watering with all the taco possibilities…
Spring is the time to plan for the year to come.//Have you taken stock of all your crops and animals yet?
It’s always good to be organized.
Can you hear that, <PlayerName>$player</>? All the trees are singing. They’re so happy it’s finally Spring.
I’m playing along with the trees, <PlayerName>$player</>. They’re so happy to be alive.//<portrait=daydreaming>Can you hear them sing?
Hey, you wanna join me and listen to the birds? They’re so cheerful right now.
I’m so glad I can eat lunch outside again. I missed doing that in Winter.
Why spend time indoors when you can be outdoors enjoying nature? Just look at all these blooming flowers!
Finally, Spring!//<portrait=daydreaming>I welcome the sound of the creatures coming back to life.
Look up, <PlayerName>$player</>! The birds are coming back, slowly but surely.//<portrait=daydreaming>Just listen to their melodious voices…
I think the daisies in Summer are nature telling us it’s happy and healthy. Don’t you think?
Since the days are longer in Summer, it’s nice to have all this time to spend outside.
It is hotter than I’d like for eating outside, but it’s much better than eating inside.//<portrait=daydreaming>Nothing beats eating in nature, not even air-conditioned rooms.
Sure, the Summer heat makes my work harder, but I’d rather sweat it out surrounded by nature than stay inside.
I’m a little sad, friend. The trees are starting to lose their leaves, and the animals are leaving.//<portrait=normal>Well, I guess I still have the animals at the ranch.

Fall is a pretty busy season for farmers, I bet. All the farming and harvesting to do.//<portrait=normal>Dad usually has lots of things for me to do to get the animals ready for Winter.//<portrait=laugh>I guess I’m busy in Fall, too!
I’m savoring all the time I can spend outside now.//<portrait=sad>In about a week, I won’t be able to enjoy the outdoors like this.
Look up, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=concerned>A lot of birds are migrating south.//Goodbye, sweet birds.//<portrait=daydreaming>I’ll see you again in Spring.
Want some of my green tea, <PlayerName>$player</>? I always carry some in Fall. It’s a nice, quick warm-up when it’s chilly.
Not gonna lie, Winter bums me out a bit. The trees are quiet, and a lot of animals either are hibernating or have migrated to somewhere warmer.
I’m not a big fan of the cold.//It’s hard to eat your lunch outside when you’re constantly shivering.
I wish I could hibernate like the bears. Sleep through the cold Winter and wake up when it’s warm again in Spring.
When it’s cold like this, there’s nothing like a cup of hot green tea to warm you up.
Winter makes me think of roasted almonds.//<portrait=normal>Hmm, maybe I’ll stop by <NPCName>Sam’s</>and buy some to roast over the fire.
Winter is always so quiet.//Hear that? Basically nothing…just faint music far, FAR away.//Don’t worry, I hear it too. It’s nature’s music.
I can’t wait to hear the birds again, <PlayerName>$player</>. I miss their songs on my morning walks.
It’s so cold that even a hot cup of green tea isn’t helping.//<portrait=sad>I should just head inside.
The hot spring sounds so good right now.
There’s a picture of me playing on your farm when I was maybe eight years old.//It’s hanging somewhere in our cabin.
This was back when it was still your grandparents’.
The bugs are always thickest in Summer.//Yesterday, I caught a wasp in the barn and released it outside.
It stung me, but I think it was just scared.
The color of the lake is so beautiful this time of year.//When you splash, the water makes little rainbows in the sunlight.
Let’s go swimming there sometime!
Have you harvested any pineapples yet? I hear they’re great grilled!
Summer heat makes moving the animals around twice as hard. It’s not so bad, though. At least it’s already light when I get up in the morning!
You definitely don’t want to smell me after work, though.
Oops! I got a little bit of pollen on my hat.//Good thing it didn’t land in my eyes!
Is there a flower nearby that I can brush it on?
Incredible how time flies, isn’t it?
I was shocked to wake up this morning and realize it’s already the 16th. *sighs*
*zones out*
Even though my parents don’t celebrate birthdays, they still love getting presents.
If you want to win my mom over, she has a soft spot for flowers.
Funbucket is one of our ducks.//But <NPCName>Ben</> comes by often to help out with the animals, and they seem to have bonded. So Funbucket is his now too.
This is the most beautiful foliage I’ve ever seen on Coral Island!
Well, I say that every year, but I really mean it this time!
I’m trying to catch as much sun as I can near the lake while it’s still Fall.//Once Winter comes, the sun is too weak to warm you up.
I guess that’s what Fishensips is good for. Nothing warms you up like a hot tea on a chilly evening!
Fall is the most delicious time of year! Nothing beats harvest time for a good meal…or five.
Do you think ranch animals notice the changing of the seasons as much as we do?//Do you think they notice the days getting shorter and the air getting colder?
Hmm… What?
<PlayerName>$player</>! I’m sorry. I just got a little lost in the color of the trees.
This island looks like a completely different place when it’s covered in snow like this.
*zones out*

Let me tell you a Winter story.//I don’t remember when it was exactly, but it was snowing out.//<portrait=smile>The kids came to me and asked me to play the flute while they sang a birthday song to <NPCName>Randy</>.
There were definitely tears that day.

Let me tell you a Winter story.//I don’t remember when it was exactly, but it was snowing out.//<portrait=smile>The kids came to me and asked me to play the flute while they sang a birthday song to <NPCName>Randy</>.
There were definitely tears that day.
Dad enters a cooking competition every year. Mom and I usually go to town to watch and give him emotional support.
He likes things like that.
One time, Mom brought home flowers that were white as snow. Very delicate flowers.
I’m no good with names. I can’t remember what they were called.//Shy flowers… They only bloom after sunset.
Are you going to the Winter Fair tomorrow?
I’m most interested in chatting with the merchants, sharing stories. They have an interesting view of the world.
Aww… Well, if you have time, you should stop by. <NpcName>Luke</> and I are going tomorrow.
Things might not be perfect, but I did my best this year, which is good enough for me.//Here’s to the New Year!
I’m glad we have a heater for the animals at the ranch.//<portrait=concerned>I hate to think about them being cold and lonely when I’m not there.
Make sure you stay bundled up, <PlayerName>$player</>. Even though we’re on an island, it can get pretty chilly here.
The plants and animals are all sleeping, tucked away under the snow. It makes me feel like I should be sleeping, too.
Our animals don’t like the rain very much.//<NPCName>Luke</> said <NpcName>Taco</> hates the rain too.//<portrait=laugh>He gets really lazy and stays inside the house all day when it rains.
I guess I’ve always known I want to work with animals.//I want to make sure they’re properly cared for.
Perhaps we can sit somewhere dry and chat.
Our animals don’t like the rain very much.//<NPCName>Luke</> said <NpcName>Taco</> hates the rain too.//<portrait=laugh>He gets really lazy and stays inside the house all day when it rains.
I guess I’ve always known I want to work with animals.//I want to make sure they’re properly cared for.
It’s getting dark, <PlayerName>$player</>…
I don’t want to spread negativity, but you should always check your barn and chicken coop during a storm.//Especially a strong one like this.
Hopefully, it won’t happen, but the wind could wreck your roof.
Keep warm, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Have you checked on your animals today?//<portrait=smile>They can use some extra love on days like this.
Animals get cold too, especially when it’s snowing like this. Make sure to turn your heater on, okay?
To keep warm during Winter, Mom used to go to the cavern and slay monsters.//<portrait=concerned>I felt kind of bad for her.
I’m curious to see how beautiful the view must be from up above.
I can imagine watching the snow as it falls.
What do you see when you see the snow, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Very wise. I must agree. Keep going with whatever project you’re working on. You’re onto something big.

Special.SourceString: Unity. That we’re all under the same blanket of existence.

Text.SourceString: Ha ha ha. That cracked me up. You’re technically correct. I concur.
Perhaps it’s a helpful reminder for us to rest. An opportunity to do something in life besides work and count our money.
The weather channel isn’t always right.//<portrait=annoyed>I got caught in the middle of a snowstorm one time on my way to Turtle Island.
<NPCName>Theo</> and I were in the middle of the ocean when it started storming.//<portrait=normal>It was fine, though. We made it to land okay.
<NPCName>Millie</> once said to me that evening snow made her feel like she was living inside a snow globe.//<portrait=daydreaming>She felt liberated yet fragile at the same time.
Ever since, I’ve thought a lot about what she said.
My dad taught me how to handle animals at a young age.//I feel like almost all my significant memories are here on this ranch.
The loudest quack is Funbucket’s.//<portrait=smile>She’s our most outspoken duck.
We could use an extra heater here.//<portrait=normal>Can I help you with anything?
Since I have you here, let me just say something really quick.//You still need to feed your animals, even though they’re out during the day.
<NPCName>Ling</> has been trying to find the right formula to improve our fodder… That’s no rumor!
Do you have enough fodder at your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Stephen was stranded and had lost his left claw when <NPCName>Macy</> rescued him…//<portrait=normal>The last time I saw him, he was recovering quite well.
I want to visit <NPCName>Stephen</> more often. He fascinates me. But I’m not too fond of the beach… Too far. The energy is all off over there.
Just thought I’d pay the <NPCName>Sanchez</> brothers a visit.//It’s been a while since we all hung out.
*mourning*
<NPCName>Luke</> was selling a self-stirring pot one time, but the product was pulled by the manufacturer before anyone had the chance to buy it.
Whoa! Excuse me for laughing.//I don’t know why that was so funny.
I’m not going to buy anything today.//Probably not the wisest choice, carrying around electronics in this weather.
Hmm… What do you think that painting over there is trying to convey?
So many thoughts went into that art piece.//<portrait=daydreaming>When I look at it, I can feel conviction and hope. Deep in my bones.
Dad sautéed a questionable fruit from the forest one time, thinking it was jackfruit.//Hmm…//<portrait=sad>The whole cabin smelled like rotten eggs for a week.
Dad’s a good cook, though.//<portrait=laugh>Just a little too adventurous for his own good sometimes.
This time of year, your cabin must be cold too.
A bit too stuffy in here at the moment.//<portrait=concerned>I think the humidity is getting to us.
Please help yourself, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>We’re all family here.
Your chickens can get really sad if you don’t feed them.//<portrait=concerned>The same goes for cows and other farm animals.
The weather channel isn’t always right.//<portrait=annoyed>I got caught in the middle of a snowstorm one time on my way to Turtle Island.
<NPCName>Theo</> and I were in the middle of the ocean when it started storming.//<portrait=normal>It was fine, though. We made it to land okay.
Lunch tastes so much better here, doesn’t it?
I remember Mom brought some weird things home from her combat journeys.//<portrait=smile>My treasure chest was full of silver spoons and colorful rocks.
I prefer to spend my time in nature.//<portrait=daydreaming>Here and the forest are two of my favorite places.

Are you familiar with <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>?//They’re <NPCName>Frank</> and <NPCName>Erika’s</> cats.//<portrait=laugh>Brilliant little fellas. They know which furniture is theirs.
Some of the paintings at Socket & Pan are <NPCName>Dippa’s</>.//They use it as a platform to market their art.
The weather channel isn’t always right.//<portrait=annoyed>I got caught in the middle of a snowstorm one time on my way to Turtle Island.
<NPCName>Theo</> and I were in the middle of the ocean when it started storming.//<portrait=normal>It was fine, though. We made it to land okay.
What if we’re just insignificant beings, living in our own little snow globe?//I’m okay with that.//<portrait=normal>What about you?//Are you okay with that?
So much to think about.
Stephen was stranded and had lost his left claw when <NPCName>Macy</> rescued him…//<portrait=normal>The last time I saw him, he was recovering quite well.
What a massive heart <NPCName>Macy</> has.
Just smell that fresh air!//<portrait=smile>I’m so lucky I get to work outside.
This might sound weird, but I don’t mind the smell of manure.//Dad was telling me it makes great fertilizer for the fields!
Is that gross?//I’m sorry. I just think it’s cool that even animal waste has a good use.
<PlayerName>$player</>, have you fed your animals yet today? They could get sick if you forget to feed them.
Whoops! I almost bumped into you!//<portrait=normal>Where are you off to in such a rush?
Make sure you take time to smell the roses! And the petunias, and the tulips, and the daisies…
What’s that amazing smell? Did you bring me a snack, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Hello, hello! None of the cows farted on me this morning, so I’m pretty sure that means it’s going to be a good day.
I took one of my tools to <NPCName>Rafael</> to have him repair it. It came back good as new!
Hopefully, <NPCName>Bessie</> won’t step on it again…
*staring into space*//<portrait=concerned>What time is it?
Oh no! Is it really that late already?//<portrait=normal>I didn’t mean to zone out for that long! Thanks for snapping me out of it, <PlayerName>$player</>.
People call Wednesday “hump day,” but I call it “moo day.”//<portrait=normal>It’s the day we bathe all the cows!
Have you spent time down by the lake, <PlayerName>$player</>?//It’s gorgeous over there.
I saw the most beautiful fish there the other day.//<portrait=daydreaming>It had this silver head and rainbow scales. I wonder if it’s rare.
Do you play any instruments, <PlayerName>$player</>? I’ve been trying to learn this new song on my flute, but it’s not going so well.
Gosh, I should check the weather forecast for tomorrow.//We’ll have to take the animals inside the barn if it rains.
<PlayerName>$player</>, have you fed your animals yet today? They could get sick if you forget to feed them.
Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>, get this!//<portrait=normal>I was about to eat my lunch yesterday when a deer wandered up next to me. I felt so bad for it that I gave it my edamame.
I was going to give the deer my water, but I don’t think it could drink out of a bottle.
It’s Friday! I can’t wait to celebrate at the tavern tonight.//<portrait=normal>Come with me?
Well, I still have to work tomorrow morning, but I’ll take any excuse to spend time with <NPCName>Frank</> and <NPCName>Pablo</>.
Mom made me scrambled eggs for breakfast, but I just can’t stand that kind of thing.//<portrait=concerned>I left it on a plate outside the house. Maybe a deer will snack on it.
Are you doing anything fun this weekend, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Me? Well, I’m hoping to head to the forest after I finish work.//I’m really trying to get this flute melody down.
Just smell that fresh air!//<portrait=smile>I’m so lucky I get to work outside.
What’s that amazing smell? Did you bring me a snack, <PlayerName>$player</>?
It’s okay if you didn’t. I made this amazing vegan taco I’m going to eat later. I can’t wait!
It’s my day off! What should I do today? There’s so much to explore around here!
Hmm… Should I go for a swim later?
Or should I play my flute?//So many choices…
The mayor was telling me the other day that you’re quite the rancher!//<portrait=normal>You’ll have to come tell me about your adventures sometime.
